Subject: Re: [T2] Elastic cord and crimper ring source?

I was able to obtain "shock cord" from a boat supply place - they sell
it in various size and color.  For the metal rings, I went to the
local hardware store and found some brass rings that fit over the
doubled-up shock cord.  I made my loop and crimped the rings with
pliers.  Looks and works same as stock.  This was on a '69 Westy.

-Josh
'69 & '77 Campmobile

